There are only 16 legislative days left this year. Things that are not getting done as House Democrats pursue their never-ending quest for impeachment:

➡️Lowering prescription drug prices
➡️Growing our economy & passing USMCA
➡️Supporting our troops & passing NDAA

This highly partisan impeachment process has been broken from day one. Today’s resolution doubles down on secrecy and continues to undermine the fundamental principles of fairness. I voted against it. https://walberg.house.gov/media/press-releases/walberg-votes-against-secretive-impeachment-inquiry-process …

For more than a month, the House’s impeachment inquiry has been conducted entirely behind closed doors. We sent a letter to Speaker Pelosi today urging her to increase transparency and due process.  https://walberg.house.gov/media/press-releases/michigan-representatives-urge-speaker-pelosi-make-impeachment-inquiry-more … pic.twitter.com/lEDFuDXKsh

It has been a privilege to serve on @HouseCommerce under @repgregwalden's solutions-oriented leadership. Greg's time in Congress is a testament to how big things can be accomplished when we work together. He will be missed.
